article.description: Kristine Anigwe had 20 points, 13 rebounds and four assists, and No. 21 California held the Colorado women to 14 first-half points on the way to a 64-35 win on Friday night.
article.headline: No. 21 California women beat Colorado 64-35
article.story:
BERKELEY, Calif. --  Kristine Anigwe had 20 points, 13 rebounds and four assists, and No. 21 California held the Colorado women to 14 first-half points on the way to a 64-35 win on Friday night.

Courtney Range added 10 points and eight rebounds for Cal (10-4, 1-2 Pac-12), which led 37-20 at the end of the third quarter and had a 13-0 run in the fourth quarter for a 58-27 lead with 4:59 left. The Golden Bears had their largest lead at 62-30.

Kennedy Leonard had 12 points to lead the Buffaloes (5-9, 0-3), who were 6 of 19 from the field in the first half with a pair of made 3-pointers and no free-throw attempts.

The Golden Bears outscored Colorado 9-0 in the second quarter to take a 23-14 lead into the half.

Colorado finished one point over the lowest total Cal has ever allowed to a Pac-12 opponent (34).
